However once you start running your auto, your robot should “reset” it’s pose to the start of the associated path.</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":15,"updated_at":"2024-01-16T20:25:24.849Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":150,"readers_count":149,"score":35.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":450504,"topic_slug":"2024-field2d-shuffleboard-widget-robot-not-starting-from-alliance","display_username":"viggy96","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":24613,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"418 Mentor | Tries to be smart"},"post_url":"/t/2024-field2d-shuffleboard-widget-robot-not-starting-from-alliance/450504/2","custom_user_title":"418 Mentor | Tries to be smart","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3286483,"name":"Can Toğran","username":"cantogr07","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/cantogr07/{size}/208647_2.png","created_at":"2024-01-17T04:05:04.981Z","cooked":"<p>Our auto has the following 2 methods and we instantiate a SendableChooser that builds every auto routine we currently have in PathPlanner.</p>
<p><div class="lightbox-wrapper"><a class="lightbox" href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/3/b/3beb623b4343da3f698cb88548d213778f484dae.png" data-download-href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/3beb623b4343da3f698cb88548d213778f484dae" title="Screenshot 2024-01-17 at 07.03.53"><img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/3/b/3beb623b4343da3f698cb88548d213778f484dae_2_690x188.png" alt="Screenshot 2024-01-17 at 07.03.53" data-base62-sha1="8y4tDBeywFUiU6TOF0ehZmTwI2i" width="690" height="188" srcset="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/3/b/3beb623b4343da3f698cb88548d213778f484dae_2_690x188.png, https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/3/b/3beb623b4343da3f698cb88548d213778f484dae_2_1035x282.png 1.5x, https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/3/b/3beb623b4343da3f698cb88548d213778f484dae_2_1380x376.png 2x" data-dominant-color="17171C"><div class="meta"><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#far-image"></use></svg><span class="filename">Screenshot 2024-01-17 at 07.03.53</span><span class="informations">1660×454 57.6 KB</span><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#discourse-expand"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>
<p>Wouldn’t PathPlanner automatically reset the Field image with respect to different starting alliances of the robot?</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":15,"updated_at":"2024-01-17T04:05:04.981Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":112,"readers_count":111,"score":37.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":450504,"topic_slug":"2024-field2d-shuffleboard-widget-robot-not-starting-from-alliance","display_username":"Can Toğran","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/3/b/3beb623b4343da3f698cb88548d213778f484dae.png","internal":true,"reflection":false,"clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":24613,"username":"viggy96","name":"viggy96","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/viggy96/{size}/252784_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":53237,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"pink dragons fly higher"},"post_url":"/t/2024-field2d-shuffleboard-widget-robot-not-starting-from-alliance/450504/3","custom_user_title":"pink dragons fly higher","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3286497,"name":"viggy96","username":"viggy96","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/viggy96/{size}/252784_2.png","created_at":"2024-01-17T04:19:54.522Z","cooked":"<p>PathPlanner transforms the point to it’s red side equivalent if necessary, but the origin remains on the blue side, always. PathPlanner should call “setPose” to set the pose to the initial pose of the path when the path starts.</p>
<p><a class="mention" href="/u/mjansen4857">@mjansen4857</a> would know better than I do.</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":15,"updated_at":"2024-01-17T04:19:54.522Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":98,"readers_count":97,"score":34.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":450504,"topic_slug":"2024-field2d-shuffleboard-widget-robot-not-starting-from-alliance","display_username":"viggy96","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":53237,"username":"cantogr07","name":"Can Toğran","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/cantogr07/{size}/208647_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":24613,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"418 Mentor | Tries to be smart"},"post_url":"/t/2024-field2d-shuffleboard-widget-robot-not-starting-from-alliance/450504/4","custom_user_title":"418 Mentor | Tries to be smart","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3286794,"name":"Michael Jansen","username":"mjansen4857","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/mjansen4857/{size}/201972_2.png","created_at":"2024-01-17T15:41:09.184Z","cooked":"<p>If your robot odom is not being reset when you run the auto then you probably don’t have a starting pose in the auto.</p>
<p>Also, your current setup would not react to the current alliance. It will always flip the path to the red side since your “should flip path” supplier is always returning true. You’d want to change this to return true only if the current alliance is red.</p>","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"posts_count":15,"updated_at":"2024-01-17T15:41:09.184Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":91,"readers_count":90,"score":43.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":450504,"topic_slug":"2024-field2d-shuffleboard-widget-robot-not-starting-from-alliance","display_username":"Michael Jansen","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":53237,"username":"cantogr07","name":"Can Toğran","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/cantogr07/{size}/208647_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":33850,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"3015 Programming Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/2024-field2d-shuffleboard-widget-robot-not-starting-from-alliance/450504/5","custom_user_title":"3015 Programming Mentor","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3286862,"name":"Cole Hunt","username":"crh_redbird1","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/crh_redbird1/{size}/237120_2.png","created_at":"2024-01-17T16:25:46.778Z","cooked":"<p>We have a similar issue so I’d figured I’d chime in here.</p>
<p>We created a ShuffleBoard button that updates the robot pose to the first point of the path. We  tried to disable the dynamic planning for initial path pose but had no luck. We are currently using the button to update our pose until we start using April Tag for localization. Is there a better method for doing this using some sort of Pathplanner configs?</p>
<p>Another issue we encountered with the Field Widget is that the coordinate frame seems to be off to the one being used in PathPlanner. When we set the robot to the first pose in the path it shows inside the drivers station on the widget. The path runs fine but the widget is off horizontality. I don’t know if this is an issue with the Widget Cords or the PathPlanner cords.</p>","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"posts_count":15,"updated_at":"2024-01-17T16:25:46.778Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":5,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":84,"readers_count":83,"score":21.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":450504,"topic_slug":"2024-field2d-shuffleboard-widget-robot-not-starting-from-alliance","display_username":"Cole Hunt","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":33850,"username":"mjansen4857","name":"Michael Jansen","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/mjansen4857/{size}/201972_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":33098,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"4143/4423 Technical Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/2024-field2d-shuffleboard-widget-robot-not-starting-from-alliance/450504/6","custom_user_title":"4143/4423 Technical Mentor","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3286884,"name":"Michael Jansen","username":"mjansen4857","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/mjansen4857/{size}/201972_2.png","created_at":"2024-01-17T16:38:42.032Z","cooked":"<p>If you want to reset your pose you’ll want to use the starting pose in an auto mode, not the first point of the path. Since you can start following a path with any rotation/velocity paths themselves don’t have a real starting pose unless you set the “preview starting rotation”. But I’d still recommend using the starting pose from an auto over that.</p>
<p>Try using AdvantageScope over shuffleboard. The AdvantageScope field coordinates are correct.</p>","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"posts_count":15,"updated_at":"2024-01-17T16:38:42.032Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":6,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":77,"readers_count":76,"score":25.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":450504,"topic_slug":"2024-field2d-shuffleboard-widget-robot-not-starting-from-alliance","display_username":"Michael Jansen","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":33098,"username":"crh_redbird1","name":"Cole Hunt","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/crh_redbird1/{size}/237120_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":33850,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"3015 Programming Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/2024-field2d-shuffleboard-widget-robot-not-starting-from-alliance/450504/7","custom_user_title":"3015 Programming Mentor","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3286889,"name":"Can Toğran","username":"cantogr07","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/cantogr07/{size}/208647_2.png","created_at":"2024-01-17T16:44:28.693Z","cooked":"<p>Thank you for your response. I got the second part and fixed the configuration method to account for red&amp;blue path flipping, however how can I reset the swerve odometry in autoInit perhaps to the starting position of the path?</p>","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"posts_count":15,"updated_at":"2024-01-17T16:44:28.693Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":5,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":65,"readers_count":64,"score":18.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":450504,"topic_slug":"2024-field2d-shuffleboard-widget-robot-not-starting-from-alliance","display_username":"Can Toğran","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":33850,"username":"mjansen4857","name":"Michael Jansen","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/mjansen4857/{size}/201972_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":53237,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"pink dragons fly higher"},"post_url":"/t/2024-field2d-shuffleboard-widget-robot-not-starting-from-alliance/450504/8","custom_user_title":"pink dragons fly higher","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3286892,"name":"Michael Jansen","username":"mjansen4857","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/mjansen4857/{size}/201972_2.png","created_at":"2024-01-17T16:46:50.118Z","cooked":"<p>Just run the PathPlannerAuto command and it will do it for you</p>","post_number":9,"post_type":1,"posts_count":15,"updated_at":"2024-01-17T16:46:50.118Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":8,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":65,"readers_count":64,"score":18.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":450504,"topic_slug":"2024-field2d-shuffleboard-widget-robot-not-starting-from-alliance","display_username":"Michael Jansen","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":53237,"username":"cantogr07","name":"Can Toğran","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/cantogr07/{size}/208647_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":33850,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"3015 Programming Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/2024-field2d-shuffleboard-widget-robot-not-starting-from-alliance/450504/9","custom_user_title":"3015 Programming Mentor","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3286914,"name":"Cole Hunt","username":"crh_redbird1","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/crh_redbird1/{size}/237120_2.png","created_at":"2024-01-17T17:01:39.533Z","cooked":"<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java">public Command setInitPose(String pathName) {
        return Commands.runOnce(
                () -&gt; {
                    PathPlannerPath path = PathPlannerPath.fromPathFile(pathName);
                    PathPoint firstPoint = path.getPoint(0);
                    Pose2d firstPose = new Pose2d(firstPoint.position, firstPoint.rotationTarget.getTarget());
                    this.resetPose(firstPose);
                }).ignoringDisable(true);
    }
</code></pre>
